<font color="#FF0000">SORRY 'BOUT THAT!</font><br>
<tt>Fri Oct 17 11:43:32 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
My Martin Baker ejection seat malfunctioned while I was picking my nose... I think I drove my finger up through my brain.<br><br>
I apologize for flaunting &quot;poor me&quot; bullshit on the site.<br><br>
Thanks Joe.. you remind me to be grateful that I lasted two years instead of an average of 170 days.  One of my classmates was shot between the eyes during is fourth day.<br><br>
I didn't mean to throw a DFC in anyone's face:  I remember evacuating a wounded machine gunner who had been shot between his liver and lungs.  His RTO was begging and crying for a medivac (must have been close friends).  One helicopter crew refused to come in because of the intensity of the automatic weapons fire and volunteered to stand by until the situation improved (prudent thinking.. not cowardice) another denied the request because they were bingo on fuel.  I went in with a Charlie Model gunship to evacuate the man (not a smart thing to do) but I expended my rockets and ammunition on the way in to make the ship lighter.  On the way back, that badly wounded enlisted man squirmed across the cargo deck, in his own blood and body fluids to get close enough to reach up and touch my elbow with his slimey fingers...he just wanted to thank me.  It broke my heart and I pushed that old gunship past its limits to save his life... and I won that one.  I wasn't decorated that time, but I was reprimanded for jeopardizing the lives of my crew (sort of like betting on a bad hand in a poker game.. if you do it enough times you will lose your ass). When my commander was through chewing my ass, he asked if I had anything to say.  The only thing I could say was..&quot;If that had been you shot all to shit and I had come in and got you..would you be complaining right now?&quot;  It was unfair for me to say that... he was a heroic man and a good leader.<br>
Bottom line... I will never forget the looks in the eyes of the men that I rescued.. nor will I forget the ones who pissed me off because they died enroute... I am tormented by the few I could not find.<br>
Please excuse this outburst.<br><br>
MTF
